# `alias l='ls -CF'` (from /etc/bash.bashrc or the user's pre-shrc
# chain) would turn `l() { ... }` into `ls -CF() { ... }` and fail with
# a syntax error -- breaking shrc entirely. Must be at top-level (not
# inside the `if is_interactive; then` compound) so it executes before
# that block is parsed and alias expansion has already taken effect on
# its body. shrc is the full interactive config, so inherited aliases
